<h2 id="tables">Tables</h2>

<p>A table would be a useful thing to include, the way to include them in markdown, or more specifically kramdown, is quite easy.</p>

<table class="table">
  <thead>
    <tr>
      <th style="text-align: left">Header1</th>
      <th style="text-align: center">Header2</th>
      <th style="text-align: right">Header3</th>
    </tr>
  </thead>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">cell 1</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">cell 2</td>
      <td style="text-align: right">cell 3</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">cell 4</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">cell 5</td>
      <td style="text-align: right">cell 6</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
  <tbody>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">cell 1</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">cell 2</td>
      <td style="text-align: right">cell 3</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">cell 4</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">cell 5</td>
      <td style="text-align: right">cell 6</td>
    </tr>
  </tbody>
  <tfoot>
    <tr>
      <td style="text-align: left">Footer 1</td>
      <td style="text-align: center">Footer 2</td>
      <td style="text-align: right">Footer 3</td>
    </tr>
  </tfoot>
</table>

<p>The table right now does not look good at all - although it is a convenient way to include a table in a markdown document. This can be fixed very easily thanks to bootstrap by adding the <code class="highlighter-rouge">{: .table}</code> attribute list definiton to opt-in to bootstraps table styling. I will have a look at how I want these to be formatted at a later date but for now it ticks all of the boxes.</p>

